🇯🇵🇺🇦At the conference on the restoration of Ukraine in Tokyo, they planned to show Zelensky’s video message, but Kyiv canceled the broadcast, moderators said.

Kisida and Shmygal spoke at the conference.

The governments of the two countries announced the need to tighten sanctions against Russia.

Kishida promised that Japan would take “five actions” to support Kyiv:

• will conclude a new tax treaty and revise investment agreements;

• will contribute to increasing the authorized capital of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development for the reconstruction of Ukraine;

• will provide a loan through the Black Sea Trade and Development Bank;

• will open an office of the Japan External Trade Development Organization in Kyiv;

• will soften the conditions for issuing multiple-entry visas to representatives of the Ukrainian side participating in bilateral projects.

